    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support acceptance. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is mitigated by the fact that the single test condition represents the worst-case clinical loading scenario. All three quantities of interest satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds across both independent laboratories. The assessment team therefore concludes that the FEA framework is credible for the stated context of use.",
